adjectives.description: forestish (comparative more forestish, superlative most forestish)

entries.meaning: (archaic, nonce word) Characteristic of a forest.
examples: The country near this place begins to look forestish. Cottages, as usual, neat, and overgrown with roses and honeysuckle, though ever so poor; a bit of lawn and gravel-walk to the door, in imitation of gentlemen's cottages.
